2026-04-16 12:34:19 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['control module internal ground return connection between battery negative, relay/sensor ground node, and output − cable terminal'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show the control module input has a good 12 V supply, and the relay coil sees the full 12 V between its two terminals, yet the module’s output remains at about 0.36 V on the ‘+’ line and near 0 V on the ‘−’ line, with no 12 V differential reaching the load. A subsequent continuity test (with power off) revealed an open circuit between battery negative and the control module’s internal ground node, and also between that internal ground node and the control output ‘−’ cable terminal. This means the entire control electronics and relay reference node are floating about 0.36 V above the true battery negative, and there is no proper 0 V return path from the relay/sensor circuit to either the power‑supply negative or the output ‘−’ lead. As a result, even with the relay contacts working, the module cannot deliver a correct 12 V/0 V pair to its outputs. The fault is therefore an open (broken track, cracked solder joint, disconnected wire or terminal) in the internal ground return of the control module between its ground node, the power‑supply negative, and the output ‘−’ cable terminal.'
